                            <handNote>Pocked in evenly-spaced strokes but vowel strokes shorter than in other inscriptions from this site. <q>Inscription pocked (up-top-down) and has to be studied carefully, especially at the top of the stone; but the reading is certain</q> (Macalister 1945, 154). Cuppage et al (1986, 264) noted that <q>the third word (presumably MAQI) can no longer be clearly traced but the reading is confirmed by Romilly Allen (1892, 260), and Macalister (1945, 154). Faint traces of scores (MAQI) on the top of the stone can be made out using raking light on the 3d model</q>.<height/>
