                    <lb n="1" style="text-direction:up"/>ṂẠQI-DECC[E]DẠ ṂQ̣Ị GLASICONAS 
                </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <p/>
            </div>
            <div type="translation">
                <p>of Mac-Deichet son of Glaisiuc</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>This is one of the inscriptions listed by McManus (1991, 94-95) in which apocope (loss of final consonants or syllables) begins to show itself (MAQI-DECCEDA (earlier -AS), cp. CIIC 66. Faunkill and the Woods, Cork: MAQI-DECCEDDAS). It may be dated to the first half of the sixth century (McManus 1991, 97).</p>
                <p>The persosnal name GLASICONAS is a compound of GLAS- 'light green, grey' and -CUNAS 'dog, hound, wolf' (McManus 1991, 102, 105).</p>
            </div>
